The Norwood Police Station commander has resigned after eNCA exposed the theft of firearms from the evidence room last year. A new station commander is set to be appointed next Friday, and the management team is expected to be reshuffled. eNCA reporter Barry Bateman has the details #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403. JOHANNESBURG - The Norwood Police Station commander has resigned. This is after eNCA exposed the theft of firearms from the evidence room last year. WATCH | Norwood Police Station | Will heads roll? A new station commander is set to be appointed next Friday, and the management team is expected to be reshuffled. There has been a big shake-up at Norwood police station after 158 firearms were stolen from the premises. The station commander has resigned and the management team is expected to be reshuffled. eNCA's Barry Bateman reports.